      "id": "9o9lRt7vfpS59rnX",
      "questionNumber": 1,
      "questionText": "If $${S_n} = \\sum\\limits_{r = 0}^n {{1 \\over {{}^n{C_r}}}} \\,\\,and\\,\\,{t_n} = \\sum\\limits_{r = 0}^n {{r \\over {{}^n{C_r}}},\\,} $$then $${{{t_{ n}}} \\over {{S_n}}}$$ is equal to ",
      "options": [
        "$${{2n - 1} \\over 2}$$ ",
        "$${1 \\over 2}n - 1$$ ",
        "n - 1",
        "$${1 \\over 2}n$$ "
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Mathematics",
      "topic": "Problems Based On Binomial Co Efficient And Collection Of Binomial Co Efficient",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "$${S_n} = \\sum\\limits_{r = 0}^n {{1 \\over {{}^n{C_r}}}}$$\n<br><br>=$${1 \\over {{}^n{C_0}}} + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_1}}} + .... + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_n}}}$$\n<br><br>$${t_n} = \\sum\\limits_{r = 0}^n {{r \\over {{}^n{C_r}}}}$$\n<br><br>= $${0 \\over {{}^n{C_0}}} + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_1}}} + {2 \\over {{}^n{C_2}}}.... + {n \\over {{}^n{C_n}}}$$.........(1)\n<br><br>We can write $${t_n}$$ by rearranging like this,\n<br><br>$${t_n}$$ = $${n \\over {{}^n{C_n}}} + {{n - 1} \\over {{}^n{C_{n - 1}}}} + ... + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_1}}} + {0 \\over {{}^n{C_0}}}$$\n<br><br>= $${n \\over {{}^n{C_0}}} + {{n - 1} \\over {{}^n{C_1}}} + ... + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_{n - 1}}}} + {0 \\over {{}^n{C_n}}}$$.........(2)\n<br><br>[as $${{}^n{C_0}}$$ = $${{}^n{C_n}}$$, $${{}^n{C_1}}$$ = $${{}^n{C_{n - 1}}}$$......]\n<br><br>By adding  (1) and (2) we get,\n<br><br>$$2{t_n}$$ = $${n \\over {{}^n{C_0}}} + {n \\over {{}^n{C_1}}} + ... + {n \\over {{}^n{C_{n - 1}}}} + {n \\over {{}^n{C_n}}}$$\n<br><br>= $$n\\left[ {{1 \\over {{}^n{C_0}}} + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_1}}} + ... + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_{n - 1}}}} + {1 \\over {{}^n{C_n}}}} \\right]$$\n<br><br>= n$${S_n}$$\n<br><br>$$\\therefore$$ $${{{t_n}} \\over {{S_n}}} = {n \\over 2}$$",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "ml8t8l1z",
      "questionNumber": 2,
      "questionText": "<p>Let $\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{r}}$ denote the coefficient of $x^{\\mathrm{r}}$ in the binomial expansion of $(1+x)^{\\mathrm{n}}, \\mathrm{n} \\in \\mathrm{N}, 0 \\leq \\mathrm{r} \\leq \\mathrm{n}$. If \n<br/><br/>$P_n=C_0-C_1+\\frac{2^2}{3} C_2-\\frac{2^3}{4} C_3+\\ldots . .+\\frac{(-2)^n}{n+1} C_n$, then the value of $\\sum\\limits_{n=1}^{25} \\frac{1}{P_{2 n}}$ equals.</p>\n",
      "options": [
        "<p>675</p>\n",
        "<p>580</p>\n",
        "<p>525</p>\n",
        "<p>650</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Mathematics",
      "topic": "Problems Based On Binomial Co Efficient And Collection Of Binomial Co Efficient",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} P_n & =\\sum_{r=0}^n \\frac{{ }^n C_r(-2)^r}{r+1}=\\sum_{r=0}^n \\frac{1}{(n+1)}{ }^{n+1} C_{r+1}(-2)^r \\\\ & =\\frac{-1}{2(n+1)} \\sum_{r=0}^n{ }^{n+1} C_{r+1}(-2)^{r+1}=\\frac{-1}{2(n+1)}\\left[(1-2)^{n+1}-1\\right] \\\\ P_n & =\\frac{1}{2(n+1)}\\left[1-(-1)^{n+1}\\right] \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} & P_{2 n}=\\frac{1}{2(2 n+1)}\\left[1-(-1)^{2 n+1}\\right] \\\\ & P_{2 n}=\\frac{1}{2 n+1} \\\\ & \\sum_{n=0} \\frac{1}{P_{2 n}}=\\sum_{n=1}^{25}(2 n+1)=3+5+\\ldots . .+51=\\frac{25}{2}[51+3]=25 \\times 27=675 \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
