      "id": "1lgzzpzqm",
      "questionNumber": 6,
      "questionText": "<p>If the coefficients of three consecutive terms in the expansion of $$(1+x)^{n}$$ are in the ratio $$1: 5: 20$$, then the coefficient of the fourth term is</p>",
      "options": [
        "3654",
        "1827",
        "5481",
        "2436"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Mathematics",
      "topic": "Problems Based On Binomial Co Efficient And Collection Of Binomial Co Efficient",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { Given: }{ }^n \\mathrm{C}_{r-1}:{ }^n \\mathrm{C}_r:{ }^n \\mathrm{C}_{r+1} \\\\\\\\\n& =1: 5: 20 \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow \\frac{n !}{(r-1) !(n-r+1) !} \\times \\frac{r !(n-r) !}{n !}=\\frac{1}{5} \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow \\frac{r}{(n-r+1)}=\\frac{1}{5} \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow 5 r=n-r+1 \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow n=6 r-1 ........(i)\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n<br/><br/>$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { Also, } \\frac{n}{r !(n-r) !} \\times \\frac{(r+1) !(n-r-1) !}{n !}=\\frac{5}{20}=\\frac{1}{20} \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow \\frac{(r+1)}{(n-r)}=\\frac{1}{4} \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow 4 r+4=n-r \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow n=5 r+4 ..........(ii)\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n<br/><br/>From (i) and (ii), we get\n<br/><br/>$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& 6 r-1=5 r+4 \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow r=5 \\\\\\\\\n& \\text { So, } n=5(5)+4=29 \\\\\\\\\n& \\text { So, coefficient of } 4{ }^{\\text {th }} \\text { terms }={ }^n \\mathrm{C}_3={ }^{29} \\mathrm{C}_3 \\\\\\\\\n& =\\frac{29 !}{3 ! 26 !}=\\frac{29 \\times 28 \\times 27}{3 \\times 2}=3654\n\\end{aligned}\n$$",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
