      "topic": "Negative And Fractional Index",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "General term of $${\\left( {1 + x} \\right)^{n}}$$ is ($${T_{r + 1}}$$) = $${{n\\left( {n - 1} \\right).....\\left( {n - r + 1} \\right)} \\over {1.2.3....r}}{x^r}$$\n<br><br>$$\\therefore$$ General term of $${\\left( {1 + x} \\right)^{27/5}}$$ = $${{{{27} \\over 5}\\left( {{{27} \\over 5} - 1} \\right).....\\left( {{{27} \\over 5} - r + 1} \\right)} \\over {1.2.3....r}}{x^r}$$\n<br><br>For first negative term, $${\\left( {{{27} \\over 5} - r + 1} \\right)}$$ &lt; 0\n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow r &gt; {{27} \\over 5} + 1$$\n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow r &gt; {{32} \\over 5}$$ \n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow r &gt; 6.4$$\n<br><br>$$\\therefore$$ r = 7\n<br><br>$${T_{7 + 1}} = {T_8}$$ means 8<sup>th</sup> term is the first negative term.",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "1ldwxb38k",
      "questionNumber": 9,
      "questionText": "<p>If $${({}^{30}{C_1})^2} + 2{({}^{30}{C_2})^2} + 3{({}^{30}{C_3})^2}\\, + \\,...\\, + \\,30{({}^{30}{C_{30}})^2} = {{\\alpha 60!} \\over {{{(30!)}^2}}}$$ then $$\\alpha$$ is equal to :</p>",
      "options": [
        "30",
        "10",
        "15",
        "60"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Mathematics",
      "topic": "Problems Based On Binomial Co Efficient And Collection Of Binomial Co Efficient",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{S}=0 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_0\\right)^2+1 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_1\\right)^2+2 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_2\\right)^2+\\ldots \\ldots+30 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_{30}\\right)^2 \\\\\\\\\n& \\mathrm{S}=30 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_0\\right)^2+29 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_1\\right)^2+28 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_2\\right)^2+\\ldots . \\cdot+0 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_0\\right)^2 \\\\\\\\\n& 2 \\mathrm{~S}=30 \\cdot\\left({ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_0{ }^2+{ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_1{ }^2+\\ldots \\ldots . \\cdot+{ }^{30} \\mathrm{C}_{30}{ }^2\\right) \\\\\\\\\n& \\mathrm{S}=15 \\cdot{ }^{60} \\mathrm{C}_{30}=15 \\cdot \\frac{60 !}{(30 !)^2} \\\\\\\\\n& \\frac{15 \\cdot 10 !}{(30 !)^2}=\\frac{\\alpha \\cdot 60 !}{(30 !)^2} \\\\\\\\\n& \\Rightarrow \\alpha=15\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n<br/><br/><b>Other Method :</b>\n<br/><br/><p>Given,</p>\n<p>$$1\\,.\\,{\\left( {{}^{30}{C_1}} \\right)^2} + 2\\,.\\,{\\left( {{}^{30}{C_2}} \\right)^2} + 3\\,.\\,{\\left( {{}^{30}{C_3}} \\right)^2}\\, + \\,.....\\, + \\,30\\,.\\,{\\left( {{}^{30}{C_{30}}} \\right)^2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\sum\\limits_{r = 1}^{30} {r\\,.\\,{{\\left( {{}^{30}{C_r}} \\right)}^2}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\sum\\limits_{r = 1}^{30} {r\\,.\\,{}^{30}{C_r}\\,.\\,{}^{30}{C_r}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\sum\\limits_{r = 1}^{30} {r\\,.\\,{{30} \\over r}\\,.\\,{}^{29}{C_{r - 1}}\\,.\\,{}^{30}{C_r}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = 30\\sum\\limits_{r = 1}^{30} {{}^{29}{C_{r - 1}}\\,.\\,{}^{30}{C_r}} $$</p>\n<p>$$ = 30 \\times $$ (Coefficient of $${x^{29}}$$ in $${(1 + x)^{59}}$$)</p>\n<p>$$ = 30 \\times \\left( {{}^{59}{C_{29}}} \\right)$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 30 \\times {{60} \\over {30}} \\times {}^{59}{C_{29}} \\times {{30} \\over {60}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 30 \\times {}^{60}{C_{30}} \\times {{30} \\over {60}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 15 \\times {{60!} \\over {30!\\,30!}}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$\\alpha  = 15$$</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
