      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Coefficient of $x^3$ in the given expression</p>\n<p>$$ (1+x)^3+(1+x)^4+\\cdots +(1+x)^{99}+(1+kx)^{100} $$</p>\n<p>is obtained by adding the coefficients of $x^3$ from each term.</p>\n<p>For $(1+x)^r$, coefficient of $x^3$ is</p>\n<p>$$ {}^rC_3 $$</p>\n<p>So, from</p>\n<p>$$ (1+x)^3+(1+x)^4+\\cdots +(1+x)^{99} $$</p>\n<p>the total coefficient of $x^3$ is</p>\n<p>$$ \\sum_{r=3}^{99} {}^rC_3 $$</p>\n<p>Also, in $(1+kx)^{100}$, coefficient of $x^3$ is</p>\n<p>$$ {}^{100}C_3\\,k^3 $$</p>\n<p>Hence total coefficient of $x^3$ is</p>\n<p>$$ \\sum_{r=3}^{99} {}^rC_3 + {}^{100}C_3 k^3 $$</p>\n<p>Now use the standard NCERT identity:</p>\n<p>$$ \\sum_{r=3}^{99} {}^rC_3 = {}^{100}C_4 $$</p>\n<p>So coefficient becomes</p>\n<p>$$ {}^{100}C_4 + {}^{100}C_3 k^3 $$</p>\n<p>Given that this equals</p>\n<p>$$ \\left(43n+\\frac{101}{4}\\right){}^{100}C_3 $$</p>\n<p>Therefore,</p>\n<p>$$ {}^{100}C_4 + {}^{100}C_3 k^3 = \\left(43n+\\frac{101}{4}\\right){}^{100}C_3 $$</p>\n<p>Divide by ${}^{100}C_3$:</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{{}^{100}C_4}{{}^{100}C_3}+k^3 = 43n+\\frac{101}{4} $$</p>\n<p>Now,</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{{}^{100}C_4}{{}^{100}C_3} = \\frac{100-3}{4} = \\frac{97}{4} $$</p>\n<p>So,</p>\n<p>$$ k^3+\\frac{97}{4}=43n+\\frac{101}{4} $$</p>\n<p>Thus,</p>\n<p>$$ k^3=43n+1 $$</p>\n<p>We need the smallest $k\\in\\mathbb N$ such that</p>\n<p>$$ k^3-1 $$</p>\n<p>is divisible by $43$.</p>\n<p>That is,</p>\n<p>$$ k^3\\equiv 1 \\pmod{43} $$</p>\n<p>Now check smallest natural numbers:</p>\n<p>$$ 1^3=1 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{43} $$</p>\n<p>So the smallest value is</p>\n<p>$$ k=1 $$</p>\n<p>Hence,</p>\n<p>$$ 1=43n+1 $$</p>\n<p>which gives</p>\n<p>$$ n=0 $$</p>\n<p>But in the question, $n\\in \\mathbb N$. In school-level convention, if $\\mathbb N=\\{0,1,2,\\dots\\}$, then this is allowed.</p>\n<p>Thus,</p>\n<p>$$ p=1,\\quad n=0 $$</p>\n<p>and</p>\n<p>$$ p+n=1 $$</p>\n<p>But this is not among the options, so clearly the intended convention is $n\\ge 1$.</p>\n<p>Now take the smallest $n\\in\\mathbb N$ with $n\\ge 1$ such that</p>\n<p>$$ k^3=43n+1 $$</p>\n<p>Try $n=1$:</p>\n<p>$$ k^3=44 \\quad \\text{not a cube} $$</p>\n<p>$n=2$:</p>\n<p>$$ k^3=87 \\quad \\text{not a cube} $$</p>\n<p>$n=3$:</p>\n<p>$$ k^3=130 \\quad \\text{not a cube} $$</p>\n<p>$n=4$:</p>\n<p>$$ k^3=173 $$</p>\n<p>$n=5$:</p>\n<p>$$ k^3=216=6^3 $$</p>\n<p>So smallest such $k$ is</p>\n<p>$$ p=6,\\quad n=5 $$</p>\n<p>Therefore,</p>\n<p>$$ p+n=6+5=11 $$</p>\n<p>Hence the correct answer is:</p>\n<p>$$ \\boxed{11} $$</p>\n<p>So, Option B is correct.</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "ofQvn9MZjWjzpi3QoA1klt9p75z",
      "questionNumber": 11,
      "questionText": "The total number of two digit numbers 'n', such that 3<sup>n</sup> + 7<sup>n</sup> is a multiple of 10, is __________.",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": null,
      "correctAnswer": "",
      "questionType": "NUMERICAL",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Mathematics",
      "topic": "Divisibility Concept And Remainder Concept",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "$$ \\because $$ $${7^n} = {(10 - 3)^n} = 10k + {( - 3)^n}$$<br><br>$${7^n} + {3^n} = 10k + {( - 3)^n} + {3^n}$$<br><br><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kqzrz1im/fb2f5714-9c20-4d0c-b22e-0b0e008f7acb/47e098e0-e298-11eb-b56b-d3be10517f29/file-1kqzrz1in-320w.png\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kqzrz1im/fb2f5714-9c20-4d0c-b22e-0b0e008f7acb/47e098e0-e298-11eb-b56b-d3be10517f29/file-1kqzrz1in-500w.png\"><source media=\"(max-width: 680px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kqzrz1im/fb2f5714-9c20-4d0c-b22e-0b0e008f7acb/47e098e0-e298-11eb-b56b-d3be10517f29/file-1kqzrz1in-680w.png\"><source media=\"(max-width: 860px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kqzrz1im/fb2f5714-9c20-4d0c-b22e-0b0e008f7acb/47e098e0-e298-11eb-b56b-d3be10517f29/file-1kqzrz1in-860w.png\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kqzrz1im/fb2f5714-9c20-4d0c-b22e-0b0e008f7acb/47e098e0-e298-11eb-b56b-d3be10517f29/file-1kqzrz1in.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 25th February Evening Shift Mathematics - Binomial Theorem Question 175 English Explanation\"></picture><br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ 3<sup>n</sup> = 3<sup>2t</sup> = (10 $$-$$ 1)<sup>t</sup><br><br>= 10p + ($$-$$1)<sup>t</sup><br><br>= 10p $$\\pm$$ 1<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ if n = even then 7<sup>n</sup> + 3<sup>n</sup> will not be multiply of 10<br><br>So if n is odd then only 7<sup>n</sup> + 3<sup>n</sup> will be multiply of 10<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ n = 11, 13, 15, ..........., 99<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ Ans : 45",
      "section": "B",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "1l5bb3q9d",
      "questionNumber": 12,
      "questionText": "<p>The remainder on dividing 1 + 3 + 3<sup>2</sup> + 3<sup>3</sup> + ..... + 3<sup>2021</sup> by 50 is _________.</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": null,
      "correctAnswer": "",
      "questionType": "NUMERICAL",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Mathematics",
      "topic": "Divisibility Concept And Remainder Concept",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Given,</p>\n<p>$$1 + 3 + {3^2} + {3^3} + \\,\\,.....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{3^{2021}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {3^0} + {3^1} + {3^2} + {3^3} + \\,\\,....\\,\\, + \\,\\,{3^{2021}}$$</p>\n<p>This is a G.P with common ratio = 3</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Sum $$ = {{1({3^{2022}} - 1)} \\over {3 - 1}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{3^{2022}} - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{{({3^2})}^{2011}} - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{{(10 - 1)}^{1011}} - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{\\left[ {{}^{1011}{C_0}\\,.\\,{{10}^{1011}} - {}^{1011}{C_1}\\,.\\,{{10}^{1010}} + \\,\\,.....\\,\\, - \\,\\,{}^{1011}{C_{1009}}\\,.\\,{{(10)}^2} + {}^{1011}{C_{1010}}\\,.\\,10 - {}^{1011}{C_{1011}}} \\right] - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{{{10}^2}\\left[ {{}^{1011}{C_0}\\,.\\,{{(10)}^{1009}} - {}^{1011}{C_1}\\,.\\,(1008) + \\,\\,.....\\,\\,{}^{1011}{C_{1009}}} \\right] + 10110 - 1 - 1} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{100k + 10110 - 2} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{100k + 10108} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50k + 5054$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50k + 50 \\times 101 + 4$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50[k + 101] + 4$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 50k' + 4$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ By dividing 50 we get remainder as 4.</p>",
      "section": "B",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "1l56ry0nx",
      "questionNumber": 13,
      "questionText": "<p>If the sum of the coefficients of all the positive powers of x, in the Binomial expansion of $${\\left( {{x^n} + {2 \\over {{x^5}}}} \\right)^7}$$ is 939, then the sum of all the possible integral values of n is _________.</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": null,
      "correctAnswer": "",
      "questionType": "NUMERICAL",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Mathematics",
      "topic": "Problems Based On Binomial Co Efficient And Collection Of Binomial Co Efficient",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Given, Binomial expression is</p>\n<p>$$ = {\\left( {{x^n} + {2 \\over {{x^5}}}} \\right)^7}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ General term</p>\n<p>$${T_{r + 1}} = {}^7{C_r}\\,.\\,{({x^n})^{7 - r}}\\,.\\,{\\left( {{2 \\over {{x^5}}}} \\right)^r}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {}^7{C_r}\\,.\\,{x^{7n - nr - 5r}}\\,.\\,{2^r}$$</p>\n<p>For positive power of x,</p>\n<p>$$7n - nr - 5r > 0$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow 7n > r(n + 5)$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow r < {{7n} \\over {n + 5}}$$</p>\n<p>As r represent term of binomial expression so r is always integer.</p>\n<p>Given that sum of coefficient is 939.</p>\n<p>When $$r = 0$$,</p>\n<p>sum of coefficient $$ = {}^7{C_0}\\,.\\,{2^0} = 1$$</p>\n<p>when $$r = 1$$,</p>\n<p>sum of coefficient $$ = {}^7{C_0}\\,.\\,{2^0} + {}^7{C_1}\\,.\\,{2^1} = 1 + 14 = 15$$</p>\n<p>when $$r = 2$$,</p>\n<p>sum of coefficient</p>\n<p>$$ = {}^7{C_0}\\,.\\,{2^0} + {}^7{C_1}\\,.\\,{2^1} + {}^7{C_2}\\,.\\,{2^2}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + 14 + 84$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 99$$</p>\n<p>when $$r = 3$$,</p>\n<p>sum of coefficient</p>\n<p>$$ = {}^7{C_0}\\,.\\,{2^0} + {}^7{C_1}\\,.\\,{2^1} + {}^7{C_2}\\,.\\,{2^2} + {}^7{C_3}\\,.\\,{2^3}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + 14 + 84 + 280$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 379$$</p>\n<p>when $$r = 4$$,</p>\n<p>sum of coefficient</p>\n<p>$$ = {}^7{C_0}\\,.\\,{2^0} + {}^7{C_1}\\,.\\,{2^1} + {}^7{C_2}\\,.\\,{2^2} + {}^7{C_3}\\,.\\,{2^3} + {}^7{C_4}\\,.\\,{2^4}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 1 + 14 + 84 + 280 + 560$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 939$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ For r = 4 sum of coefficient = 939</p>\n<p>To get value of r = 4, value of $${{7n} \\over {n + 5}}$$ should be between 4 and 5.</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$4 < {{7n} \\over {n + 5}} < 5$$</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow 4n + 20 < 7n < 5n + 25$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$4n + 20 < 7n$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow 3n > 20$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow n > {{20} \\over 3}$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow n > 6.66$$</p>\n<p>and</p>\n<p>$$7n < 5n + 25$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow 2n < 25$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow n < 12.5$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$6.66 < n < 12.5$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Possible integer values of $$n = 7,8,9,10,11,12$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Sum of values of $$n = 7 + 8 + 9 + 10 + 11 + 12$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 57$$</p>",
      "section": "B",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "n2K8x8uBYrxmQfciha7k9k2k5itwjym",
      "questionNumber": 14,
      "questionText": "The coefficient of x<sup>4</sup> is the expansion of\n(1 + x + x<sup>2</sup>)<sup>10</sup> is _____.",
      "options": [],
